a placated population is often taken for granted,

82
00:06:44.710 --> 00:06:49.530
and there is not a whole lot of time given
to depicting how or why that population is

83
00:06:49.530 --> 00:06:50.530
the way it is.

84
00:06:50.530 --> 00:06:55.449
The important part, for this media, is that
things are the way they are because the heroes

85
00:06:55.449 --> 00:06:57.580
need an oppressive force to fight against.

86
00:06:57.580 --> 00:07:01.100
They cannot conduct these battles in the open
for fear of prying eyes.

87
00:07:01.100 --> 00:07:05.680
OR, (and this is more common in American dystopian
fiction) you’ll get the flipside where the

88
00:07:05.680 --> 00:07:10.900
government has a much more active role in
using martial law to oppress the population.

89
00:07:10.900 --> 00:07:15.470
The populace is very aware that it is being
oppressed, and is usually depicted as waiting

90
00:07:15.470 --> 00:07:18.470
for the first available excuse to spark the
revolution.

91
00:07:18.470 --> 00:07:23.430
Americans love to think they’d rise up in
revolution against a tin pot dictator, but

92
00:07:23.430 --> 00:07:27.930
y'all have been awful quiet about the Supreme
Court taking away your rights.

93
00:07:27.930 --> 00:07:28.930
Anyway.

94
00:07:28.930 --> 00:07:32.490
In the former instance, however, and I feel
this is much closer to reality, the population

95
00:07:32.490 --> 00:07:36.400
does not know they are being oppressed, and
therefore have no context for freedom.

96
00:07:36.400 --> 00:07:41.039
If an oppressed people believe they are already
free, they will not pursue freedom.

97
00:07:41.039 --> 00:07:45.720
In fact, because a significant portion of
the population is comfortable in its own oppression,

98
00:07:45.720 --> 00:07:50.150
it will actively resist any change in the
status quo.

99
00:07:50.150 --> 00:07:54.120
People who can contextualise this idea of
freedom are those who can either read patterns

100
00:07:54.120 --> 00:07:58.780
objectively, or those who exist outside of
social norms and constructs.

101
00:07:58.780 --> 00:08:02.120
This is the first observation made in George
Orwell’s 1984.

102
00:08:02.120 --> 00:08:07.169
The state is dependent on intellectuals to
research and apply totalitarian principals

103
